    <stitle>DIAMONDLIFE&#8482; (BOSCH PIN SLIDE) DISC BRAKES For Vehicles Built Before June 3, 2002 - OPERATION -
        ROTOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ROTOR</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404007">Figure 7</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <para>The rotor (Item 1) is bolted to the wheel hub assembly (Item 2 ) in the same manner as brake drums.
            Cooling fins (Item 3 ) cast between the machined braking surfaces of the rotor allow air to flow between the
            rotor braking surfaces while the wheel turns.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0404007" figsize="col-wide">
